 <unitdate normal="1884/1894" type="inclusive">1884-1894</unitdate>
        <unittitle>Letters from Andrew D. White to Ernest W. Huffcutt</unittitle>
       </did>
       <scopecontent><p>Letters from Andrew D. White to Ernest W. Huffcutt suggesting that Huffcutt write history of the Cornell University, November 27, 1893, Jan. 11, 1894, August 14, 1894; relating to White's aid to Huffcutt's history of Cornell Univ. Feb. 1894; to White's relationship to Hewett's history of Cornell Univ. Feb. 1894, April 30, 1894; to student disturbances at Cascadilla, Mar. 6, 1885; to punishing officers of those classes engaged in rush, Oct. 6, 1884; to General George S. Batcheller, July 13, 1894; instructing Huffcutt on handling University business on his behalf, 1884-1885. 27 letters including resignation, all letters complete.</p></scopecontent>
